Bao Viet Holdings Shares Rise Most in a Month on Earnings Target

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-20T05:12:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/bao-viet-holdings-shares-rise-most-in-a-month-on-earnings-target.html
Bao Viet Holdings,  Vietnam ’s
largest insurer, surged the most in more than a month after the
company said it will target annual profit of as much as 1.7
trillion dong ($81.3 million) by 2015.  Bao Viet, which had 953 billion dong of profit last year,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg, climbed 4.7 percent to
78,500 dong at 11 a.m. local-time close, the biggest advance
since March 10. The benchmark VN Index of Vietnamese stocks on
the Ho Chi Minh City Stock Exchange gained 1.1 percent to
458.50.  The Hanoi-based company that’s 18 percent owned by by  HSBC
Holdings Plc (HSBA)  also announced that it will pay a 2010 dividend of
1,200 dong per share, without specifying a payment date,
according to a filing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  